fulltitle: Book Discussion on Gary Webb and `Kill the Messenger`
title: Book Discussion on Gary Webb and `Kill the Messenger`
_filename: _Book Discussion on Gary Webb and `Kill the Messenger`.mp4
description:
For more related content, please visit: https://archive.org/details/@altviewstv-fanclub

Nick Schou talked about his book Kill the Messenger: How the CIA’s Crack-Cocaine Controversy Destroyed Journalist Gary Webb, published by Nation Books. The book details the story of Gary Webb, a reporter who wrote a 1996 newspaper series linking the Central Intelligence Agency to cocaine distribution in Los Angeles. Mr. Webb’s reports were dismissed by many major news organizations, but the book’s author, Nick Schou, argues that it was not Mr. Webb, but his editors, who sensationalized the story. Mr. Webb committed suicide in 2004. Mr. Schou was interviewed on the BookTV Bus while at the Los Angeles Times Festival of Books.
